3. Symbolic Links (Advanced)
On macOS or Linux, you can create a "symlink" (symbolic link) from a folder in your repository to a folder
inside your Obsidian vault. Obsidian will treat the symlinked folder as if it were natively part of the vault,
allowing you to view and edit those repository notes without moving them. 
Pro Tip: If you choose to sync your entire vault with Git, make sure to add .obsidian/ to your .gitignore
file if you don't want your workspace settings (like open tabs) to sync across all devices. 

